net.proteusframework.core.hibernate.model

Class AbstractEntity<ID extends java.io.Serializable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.core.hibernate.model.AbstractEntity<ID>
  • Type Parameters:
    ID - the entity identifier type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Entity<ID>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractNamedEntity

    @MappedSuperclass
public abstract class AbstractEntity<ID extends java.io.Serializable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Entity<ID>
    A MappedSuperclass for implementing an Entity. This is only used for convenience, and should always be maintained as transparent to persistence code in case a subclass needs to be refactored to not use this class.
    Author:
    Kevin Beaty (kbeaty@i2rd.com)
